column1: 179077;instagram;2019-01-13 18:45:45;FALSE;"💜 no temes ir sola de noche?
mamá la vida me ha dado coraje
para salir sin miedo a matar.
para que no nos podais doblegar
tan solo queremos algo de equidad...
que no es por la ropa
que no es por la hora
a la que hay que encerrar.
sacas las llaves 4 calles más allá
pero no te asegura que vayas a llegar.
cada 4 horas en españa es abusada
hermanas temporeras a la par que la manada
y en la mani no hubo opción a decir nada
feminismo colonial y como no es marca españa.
haceis de una lucha una moda y un juego(x3)
pero de las personas que sufren? me acuerdo
la vida no es una mierda
mucha mierda hay en la vida
y eso hace que lo parezca.
ni de horas ni de prendas.

column1: 179150;instagram;2019-01-13 20:22:50;FALSE;"some things you may not know about our free event on january 20th- that's in one week ladies.

column5: equally full of wisdom and willing to listen and spend time with one another.

ماهنامه خط صلح – کمپین ۱۶ روز فعالیت علیه #خشونت_جنسی-جنسیتی، یکی از طولانی ترین و پربارترین کارزارهای جهانی برای حقوق انسانی #زنان است. این کمپین در سال ۱۹۹۱ توسط ۲۳ تن از فمنیست های کشورهای شمال (آمریکا، کانادا و اروپا) و کشورهای جنوب (کشورهای سه قاره آسیا، آفریقا و آمریکای لاتین) تحت ریاست موسسه رهبری جهانی زنان که در دانشگاه راتگرز آمریکا است، آغاز به کار کرد. آغاز و پایان ۱۶ روز فعالیت جهانی علیه خشونت های جنسی-جنسیتی با این نیت در نظر گرفته شده بود که خشونت علیه زنان را به مثابه نقض حقوق اسنانی زنان مسجل نماید. آغاز ۱۶ روز، ۲۵ نوامبر روز جهانی مبارزه با خشونت علیه زنان و پایان آن، ۱۰ دسامبر روز جهانی حقوق بشر است. در خلال این ۱۶ روز، مناسبت های جهانی دیگری نیز وجود دارد که در راستای حقوق انسانی زنان و مقابله با خشونت علیه زنان است؛ از جمله ۲۹ نوامبر، روز جهانی مدافعان زن حقوق بشر، ۱ دسامبر، روز جهانی ایدز و ۶ دسامبر سالگرد قتل عام مونترال. پیوند نمادین آغاز و پایان این ۱۶ روز، با درایت فراوان و هدفمند در یک برهه از مبارزات جهانی زنان برگزیده شده بود. در خلال دهه ۱۹۸۰-۱۹۷۰، جنبش جهانی زنان از حاشیه به مرکز توجهات جامعه جهانی سوق پیدا کرده بود. کنفرانس زنان سازمان ملل در سال ۱۹۷۵ در مکزیکوسیتی و سپسس در سال ۱۹۸۰ در کپنهاگن، فمنیست ها و فعالان حقوق برابر زنان کشورهای شمال و جنوب را در ارتباط نزدیکی قرار داده بود. در سال ۱۹۸۵، کنفرانس سوم زنان سازمان ملل در نایروبی برگزار شد. ۴ سال بعد از این کنفرانس بود که موسسه رهبری جهانی زنان، به ریاست شارلوت بانچ کارزار جهانی را آغاز نمود.

در خلال ۲۷ سال گذشته، متجاوز از ۶ هزار سازمان زنان و نهادهای مدنی در این کارزار حضور پیدا کرده و در ابعاد ملی و بین المللی، فرهنگ سازی قابل تحسینی در زمینه فرایندهای خشونت علیه زنان صورت گرفته است. فعالان حقوق زنان و فمنیست ها، در ۱۹۷ کشور ادبیاتی را که در خلال این ۲۷ سال توسط نهادهای غیردولتی و سازمان ملل ارائه داده شده، به زبان های محلی خود ترجمه کرده و در دهه اخیر به یمن تکنولوژی ارتباطی و رسانه های اجتماعی، ابعاد اطلاع رسانی در زمینه تم های برگزیده این کارزار، به طرز چشم گیری گسترده تر شده است. من خود این فرصت را داشتم که از سال ۱۹۹۱ در سمت مدیریت شبکه ائتلاف زنان آسیا و خاورمیانه و سپس شبکه بنیاد فرهنگی زنان -که سمت مشاوره با سازمان ملل را نیز دارد-، در این کارزار هرساله شرکت کنم و از نزدیک شاهد رشد و اعتلای آن باشم.";;en;#خشونت_جنسی-جنسیتی،
اقدام جهانی برای کنوانسیون رفع خشونت در محیط کار/ الهه امانی

فرهنگ سازی قابل تحسینی در زمینه فرایندهای خشونت علیه زنان صورت گرفته است . فعالان حقوق زنان و فمنیست ها، در ۱۹۷ کشور ادبیاتی را که در خلال این ۲۷ سال توسط نهادهای غیردولتی و سازمان ملل ارائه داده شده، به زبان های محلی خود ترجمه کرده و در دهه اخیر به یمن تکنولوژی ارتباطی و رسانه های اجتماعی، ابعاد اطلاع رسانی در زمینه تم های برگزیده این کارزار، به طرز چشم گیری گسترده تر شده است . من خود این فرصت را داشتم که از سال ۱۹۹۱ در سمت مدیریت شبکه ائتلاف زنان آسیا و خاورمیانه و سپس شبکه بنیاد فرهنگی زنان -که سمت مشاوره با سازمان ملل را نیز دارد-، در این کارزار هرساله شرکت کنم و از نزدیک شاهد رشد و اعتلای آن باشم .;. اقدام جهانی برای کنوانسیون رفع خشونت در محیط کار/ الهه امانی ماهنامه خط صلح – کمپین ۱۶ روز فعالیت علیه یکی از طولانی ترین و پربارترین کارزارهای جهانی برای حقوق انسانی است . این کمپین در سال ۱۹۹۱ توسط ۲۳ تن از فمنیست های کشورهای شمال ( آمریکا، کانادا و اروپا ) و کشورهای جنوب ( کشورهای سه قاره آسیا، آفریقا و آمریکای لاتین ) تحت ریاست موسسه رهبری جهانی زنان که در دانشگاه راتگرز آمریکا است، آغاز به کار کرد . آغاز و پایان ۱۶ روز فعالیت جهانی علیه خشونت های جنسی-جنسیتی با این نیت در نظر گرفته شده بود که خشونت علیه زنان را به مثابه نقض حقوق اسنانی زنان مسجل نماید . آغاز ۱۶ روز، ۲۵ نوامبر روز جهانی مبارزه با خشونت علیه زنان و پایان آن، ۱۰ دسامبر روز جهانی حقوق بشر است . در خلال این ۱۶ روز، مناسبت های جهانی دیگری نیز وجود دارد که در راستای حقوق انسانی زنان و مقابله با خشونت علیه زنان است؛ از جمله ۲۹ نوامبر، روز جهانی مدافعان زن حقوق بشر، ۱ دسامبر، روز جهانی ایدز و ۶ دسامبر سالگرد قتل عام مونترال . پیوند نمادین آغاز و پایان این ۱۶ روز، با درایت فراوان و هدفمند در یک برهه از مبارزات جهانی زنان برگزیده شده بود . در خلال دهه ۱۹۸۰-۱۹۷۰، جنبش جهانی زنان از حاشیه به مرکز توجهات جامعه جهانی سوق پیدا کرده بود . کنفرانس زنان سازمان ملل در سال ۱۹۷۵ در مکزیکوسیتی و سپسس در سال ۱۹۸۰ در کپنهاگن، فمنیست ها و فعالان حقوق برابر زنان کشورهای شمال و جنوب را در ارتباط نزدیکی قرار داده بود . در سال ۱۹۸۵، کنفرانس سوم زنان سازمان ملل در نایروبی برگزار شد . ۴ سال بعد از این کنفرانس بود که column1: a study published on sage journals found that girls of colour  who are victims of abuse are more likely to be labelled in the criminal justice system as ‘offenders’ compared to white girls who are often treated as victims.
when will the state start protecting black girls and girls of colour?
why does the state still believe that girls of colour cannot be victimised?
the #metoo movement isn’t a movement if it doesn’t include black women and women of colour.
so #timesup on this lack of inclusivity and hello to #intersectionalfeminism where black girls and women of colour are included and protected just as much as anyone else.

column2: the one that took the longest time to come to terms with during recovery
column3: one of my greatest triggers for using and drinking. this was the first time i was sexually assaulted
column4: i would be assaulted again by him and the man after him. it happened on a sunny thanksgiving day in 2011 when i lived in oakville. he always talked down to me as a person and only made sure to tell me i had the perfect body for sex and that i was pretty much only good for sexual pleasure. when i would refuse sex he would say he wanted to “make love” so i would agree
column5: and would use many other ploys to get me to keep sleeping with him when i was trying to indicate i wanted more then just that. at one point i realized if i wasn’t under the influence of alcohol
column6: i wouldn’t be able to handle our dynamic. it’s what kept me numb and able to escape the pain he caused me. it was while we were together i became an alcoholic. when i had a coworker help me pluck up the courage to cut him off
column7: he made sure to make me feel like the bad guy for doing so. he always made me feel like the bad guy when i stood my ground. he was abusive in every sense. #spiritualwarrior #wedorecover #metoo #sexualassault #artist #art #illustrator #designer #mystory;;en;#spiritualwarrior

179230;instagram;2019-01-13 22:27:42;FALSE;"*cycle of child sexual abuse: links between being a victim and becoming a perpetrator.* background: there is widespread belief in a 'cycle' of child sexual abuse
column2: but little empirical evidence for this belief.

column1: aims: to identify perpetrators of such abuse who had been victims of paedophilia and/or incest
column2: in order to: ascertain whether subjects who had been victims become perpetrators of such abuse; compare characteristics of those who had and had not been victims; and review psychodynamic ideas thought to underlie the behaviour of perpetrators.

column1: method: retrospective clinical case note review of 843 subjects attending a specialist forensic psychotherapy centre.

results: among 747 males the risk of being a perpetrator was positively correlated with reported sexual abuse victim experiences. the overall rate of having been a victim was 35% for perpetrators and 11% for non-perpetrators. of the 96 females
column2: 43% had been victims but only one was a perpetrator. a high percentage of male subjects abused in childhood by a female relative became perpetrators. having been a victim was a strong predictor of becoming a perpetrator
column3: as was an index of parental loss in childhood.

column1: conclusions: the data support the notion of a victim-to-victimiser cycle in a minority of male perpetrators but not among the female victims studied. sexual abuse by a female in childhood may be a risk factor for a cycle of abuse in males.

column1: 179296;instagram;2019-01-14 00:04:54;FALSE;this marks a year when a moment changed my life. the time in my life when i have never felt so broken and used. it is a day that i never would wish even on my worst enemy. this is the day i was raped. it isn’t something i want to spend any time or energy on. i am feeling that wound open stinging with the same intensity as the moment it was happening. this was the day when my words meant nothing to someone. when my mind and who i was
column2: was thrown away and i became an object. fulfilling someone’s filthy desires when i explicitly stated “no.” i was lied to and manipulated by this man. daniel lee hutson. i was raped in the parking lot where one year prior i took my prom photos. triple creek park
column3: specifically at the dog park. i was locked in the car
column4: and one of my many therapists i’ve seen told me that i should have had the power to get out. i do not know where to begin this story
column5: but i am trying my best. i confronted daniel about cheating. we agreed to go and get ice cream to talk things out. we took his car. he was in the mood for something else. he unzipped his pants and forced my face onto him. i said
column6: “no.” i said it multiple times. no matter how many times i would have said it
column7: it wouldn’t change his mind. he was determined to get what he wanted from me. it was around 8 o’clock when we left for ice cream. he locked the doors and took off my pants and shirt. he pulled me on top and forced me there. i said “no.” he penetrated me and fingered me
column8: to the point where blood streamed down his middle finger down to his wrist. i was in pain. mentally and physically. i cannot look at another 2002 honda accord the same ever again. i can never feel lower than i did at that moment. this is how i was raped. no protection or anything. this is when i became an object. no agency or choice in the matter. used against my will because i am physically weaker than someone. my words had no power in that moment. i am diagnosed with ptsd because of this moment. i was broken glass. i kept this to myself for a month after the event

column1: 179297;instagram;2019-01-14 00:05:14;FALSE;the emotions and pain i feel are real. i cannot thank my family enough for the love and support they have shown me. they never gave up on me
column2: even when i gave up on myself. i still struggle finding that love in myself every day. i am a survivor. my only intention for writing this down is to put it out there that rape does happen and it is real. i am still here
column3: i am still myself and i am taking back the power daniel stole from me. i have been given an amazing opportunity to start over and build my strength up every day. i have learned so many lessons at such a young age. this event is a part of who i am
column4: but it does not define me. i am learning everyday how i can be the best person i can be. to understand and be there for someone when they are struggling. i learned how to put my foot down and make sure that my power and light isn’t taken away by the darkness ever again. i am here to fight for anyone who needs a warrior. i will be here to listen
column5: even on your darkest days. i learned that i am not weak
column6: meaningless or easy. i am strong
column9: and that i can get through anything. i am proud of the progress i have made in 365 days. i am still learning and stumbling along in this life
column10: but i know for a fact of who i am. it is my responsibility to defend that. it is bittersweet to say

column1: 年末に読み終わってたんだけど、レビューできてなかった本。
背景や現状が違うとはいえ、かなり重なるところがあって、他人事とは思えなかった。
子どもの頃に感じていた違和感、「そういうもの」として疑問にも思っていなかったこと、いろんなことを思い出す。
ジェンダーギャップ指数が149か国中110位台の韓国と日本。
今年に入ってまだ2週間なのに、#西武 の #パイ投げ広告 #ピーチジョン の #ラブポーション の広告、#spa の #女子大 #女子大生 #侮辱特集、#ngt48 #山口真帆 さんの #暴行被害 、その件に関する #松本人志 の #セクハラ発言 など、去年 #伊藤詩織 さんや #metoo のムーブメントのおかげでほんの少しずつ変わってきていると思ってた(実際変わりつつあると思うけど)。
でも、まだまだ世の中を動かしている世代の人間の脳内は所詮この程度で他人事で(男も女も)、企画を通すにはいろんな人の目が入るはずなのに誰も「これはまずい」と言えず(言っても却下されるのかもしれないけどそんなことは関係ない)疑問も持たず・・・
書いていると暗い気持ちになってくるけど、「こういうもの」「仕方ない」「変わりっこない」って思って関心を持たないことが1番かっこ悪い。
自分に子どもが生まれたら？
性差別を受けてほしくない、性犯罪に遭ってほしくない、人を大切にできない人間になってほしくない・・・
そう思うのって当たり前じゃない？

column1: 179305;instagram;2019-01-14 00:34:30;FALSE;"thank you to my friend and writer alexandra israel (@zandee88) for an amazing interview featured on @cultbytes. read more about my inspiration to curate resurge and what to expect from me in 2019. link in bio.
ai: is the work or the exhibition in any way a reflection of the me-too movement?

sc: definitely. it is a direct response to the me-too movement. linda nochlin’s “why have there been no great woman artists?” also inspired me to put on the curator hat. nochlin asked the difficult but discernible problems in society and the arts. i feel that it’s important to cultivate environments and communities where female artists can thrive. gender disparity in the arts is being brought to light more than ever with the me-too movement forcing the industry to address opportunities for women artists in galleries and museums. i’ve gotten to witness first-hand the tribulations of emerging women artists and the male-dominated art scene in chelsea.
i want to celebrate women and non-binary artists
column2: specifically the artists in resurge. although society says that woman are fueled by competition
column3: my experience at mason gross was anything but. there was no hierarchy between concentrations – the painters were no better than the photographers
column4: the photographers no better than the graphic designers. i felt motivated and supported by the women artists in my class.

column2: i’m proud to share that i have been accepted into resilience chicago’s medical advocate/rape crisis counselor program
column3: and by march i will be advocating for/counseling survivors of sexual assault/violence in chicago hospitals. my volunteer work with resilience will be in addition to my usual obligations so life is going to get very busy
column4: but i am very happy to have this opportunity. like many of us
column5: over the past few years i have become more involved in the call to support women’s rights and end sexual violence. with
column10: and the recent r. kelly protests
column11: it has almost become impossible not to get involved in some way. ever since i had the powerful experience of participating in the women’s march on washington in 2017 i knew i wanted to become more involved. since then i have participated in social media activism
column12: made donations and showed my support for various organizations
column13: especially the wonderful @thejhf. becoming an advocate/counselor seemed like a natural next step. i’ve never done anything like this before so it will be a new journey
column14: probably a difficult one at times due to the nature of the work and the 60 hours of training that i will complete. but doing this feels very right for me and i’m looking forward to getting to make a difference in the lives of some of those who have been violated in the worst ways. unsurprisingly
column15: it is @therealmariskahargitay who has inspired me to take this step. without her and her activism the prospect of becoming an advocate/rape counselor probably would never have been something i thought i should/could do. but mariska has taught us that all we need to do is care and anything is possible. she has also taught us about the payoff of being fearless. this is what i will be thinking about during difficult moments of this journey. since this is a supportive community that strongly believes in the cause
column16: i plan to share some of the process with you in the hope that others may be inspired to become advocates. #mariskahargitay #fearlessness #nomore #youmatter #believesurvivors #endthebacklog #iamevidence #svu;;en;#MeToo

column1: 179441;instagram;2019-01-14 03:13:21;FALSE;"the ninth form submission to the survivor tree project was sent by a young woman named myah- mae. myah-mae’s story begins at the age of 15
column2: when she began seeing a boy who repeatedly violated her over the course of their relationship. her abuser told someone else what he’d done
column3: and myah-mae was unexpectedly confronted by a police officer at her home
column4: where she was questioned her in front of her parents. not wanting to anger her boyfriend or humiliate her family- and not knowing that what had happened to her was rape- she told the officer nothing. and the abuse continued. eventually- after repeated stalkings and harassment- she was able to get away from her abuser and seek counseling. one year later
column5: she went back to police and told them what happened
column6: and a formal investigation is now underway. •

column1: though myah-mae’s story is tinged by fear
column2: it is also illuminated by a kind of courage that many survivors are never able to find: in addition to getting away from her abusive intimate partner
column3: the bravery of seeking justice. of pressing charges. and despite not knowing what happens next
column4: she speaks of knowing that this course of action is what’s right for her. she never says it was easy- she told me of an instance where she was victim-shamed by someone who said that by staying with him for so long
column5: she consented to his abuse (which is not true. consent should be involved *each* and *every* time
column6: and it can be taken away at any time- that should be respected. always). but this has not broken her stride. her voice in telling her story is firm and unwavering. @myahmae i am so inspired by you. every survivor’s story should end with getting justice for what they’ve been through. and until that is true
column7: i will keep sharing stories like yours in hopes that it brings other survivors out of the shadows of fear and inspires them to speak their truths- loudly and unashamedly. thank you. ✨🌱 click the link in my bio if others would like to contribute your story to the survivor tree project. #survivor #survivoradvocate #believesurvivors #believewomen #rapesurvivor #sexualassaultsurvivor #metoo #timesup #endrapeculture #metoomovement #thesurvivortreeproject #artist";;en;#survivor

column1: 179459;instagram;2019-01-14 03:32:03;FALSE;"i wish i had left earlier so she wasn’t dealing with this.... “i hear the screams. the doors banging. people yelling. him chasing my brother around the table. the threats. being dragged upstairs by a brother and locked in his bedroom trying to distract me. you were sobbing in the toilet”. almost 4 years after we split up my daughter has told me this is what she’s dealing with in her head.
our kids remember what they experienced. she doesn’t remember any good times. only the screams. the abuse.
i should have left earlier and i wish i had.

please get help if you’re in an abusive relationship. please. your kids - and you - deserve a life where they feel safe... #rape #violence #ptsd  #ptsdawareness  #cptsdawareness #childabuse #scarredforlife #mentalhealthawareness #depression #itgetsbesser #metoo #maritalrape #sexualabuse #emotionalabuse #mentalabuse #abuse #domesticviolenceawareness #domesticabuse #followme #followforfollowback";;en;#rape

column1: it took me longer than i wanted to get this out because it took me time to get through surviving r kelly. it was hard to watch. i encourage you to watch it. i lived in miami when the initial video of him urinating on that young girl came out. i found out about it because i was in a gay club on south beach and they played the fucking video remixed with his music. i could not believe it. that shit stuck with me forever. i thought to myself - well at least that’s the end of his career right? ha! that’s not how it works in a patriarchy especially when wrapped in capitalism. as long as you can still make people money - you are still valuable. exploit and abuse women - no problem. exploit and abuse young black women - even less of a problem. that’s the reality of what we are seeing so clearly illustrated right now. pay attention to how it works...this is how we start to dismantle it. fuck r kelly. his studio is in chicago (at 219 n justine street). people know him. he’s around town. just living his life. folks are holding #muterkelly protests at his studio. the police are investigating because they believe some of the women are being held there. #muterkelly #blm #blacklivesmatter #patriarchy #capitalism #feminism #feminist #craftivism #craftivist #badasscrossstitch #resist #metoo #timeisup";en;#Repost

14 - victim blaming dalam kasus kekerasan seksual
menyalahkan korban pemerkosaan atau victim blaming seringkali terjadi pada pengungkapan kasus pemerkosaan
column2: termasuk di indonesia. budaya ini muncul karena banyak pihak masih menilai korban perkosaan dengan pandangan yang timpang.

column1: salah satu contoh victim blaming yang terjadi di indonesia adalah pada kasus kekerasan seksual yang dialami agni
column2: mahasiswi ugm saat melaksanakan kuliah kerja nyata.

column1: salah satu anggota departemen pengabdian kepada masyarakat (dpkm) ugm pun awalnya enggan menyebut bahwa agni adalah korban. “jangan menyebut dia (agni) korban dulu. ibarat kucing kalau diberi gereh (ikan asin dalam bahasa jawa) pasti kan setidak-tidaknya akan dicium-cium atau dimakan
column2: ” ujar orang tersebut seperti dikutip fimela dari balairung press.

column1: contoh di atas mungkin sudah cukup menggambarkan betapa ‘jahatnya’ mayoritas masyarakat terhadap korban kejahatan seksual.  bukannya berempati
column2: malah menyalahkan korban karena cara berpakaian
column3: atau hal hal yang mempengaruhi pelaku.

column2: masyarakat dituntut untuk memberikan rasa empati terhadap korban kekerasan seksual
column3: utamanya korban pemerkosaan dan tidak menyalahkan korban. cobalah untuk tidak menanyakan hal hal sensitif terhadap korban dan buat mereka nyaman
column4: supaya korban tidak merasa jiwanya tertekan.

column1: 해당 토론회에서는 안희정 성폭력사건을 중심으로 지난 1심 재판부의 위력 판단의 전반적인 문제점과 개별 공소사실에 대한 판단의 문제점을 짚고
행위수단으로서의 현행법상의 위력과 우월적 지위에 의한 범죄 관련한 해외 입법례 검토를 통해
현행 위력 성폭력의 판단기준의 문제점을 짚어보고 피해의 맥락을 반영한 ‘정의로운 판단기준’을 논의하는 장을 마련하고자 합니다.

column1: last night...a group of brave men and women came together for the first co-healing circle. 1 men's circle and 1 women's circle...becoming one. in the deafening silence we quickly realized we were standing on new territory. we arrived on the shores of our comfort zone
column2: behind us...a trail of broken hearts.⁣

column1: the air was thick and our first words had difficulty travelling through the space. our inner compass brought us here but...why? maybe the answer is so ancient we can't even remember. but we started this quest probably ages ago. this journey...into the heart.⁣
were we still on the right track? the first tear answered: yes. then the first smile said: hell yes! then more tears...and more smiles. ⁣
what walls have we build between us and our sisters...our brothers...our lovers? what is preventing us from connecting deeper? ⁣
the clothes on our body..the shame around our sexuality...the masks we wear...because we are too scared to see and be seen for who and what we really are? ⁣
yes. we arrived...at the dawn of a new reality. first footsteps in the sand. leaving the troubled waters behind to explore together...what's beyond the horizon of this new world. ⁣

column1: 179539;instagram;2019-01-14 06:50:37;FALSE;"for real though. sometimes you're like i need this person out of my life. then you block
column3: sometimes you realize it's not about them it's about a whole construct you are detoxing!  they try to come back through someone else in your life and you have to request a boundary there in an awkward conversation. boundary gets breached when said person shows up at a party your mutual friend throws. at furst you're ok and that fine.  then you realize you're not. so leave. when you do it you will feel so damn liberated .  don't answer the text .  let them transform too. if they come back may it be in a healthier renewed way . on your future healthy self level ! xo

column2: ಬೇಜಾರು ದುಃಖ ಮತ್ತು ಭಯ ಎಲ್ಲನ್ನೂ ಇದೆ...ಕಾರಣ ಚಿತ್ರ ಶುರು ಮಾಡುವಾಗ ಇಂಡಸ್ಟ್ರಿಯ ಒಂದಿಷ್ಟು ನಾಯಿ ನರಿ ಕ್ರೀಮಿ ಕೀಟಗಳು ನಾವ್ ಇದ್ದೀವಿ ಶುರು ಮಾಡಿ ಅಂತ ಹೇಳಿದವರು ಇವಾಗ ಚಿತ್ರದ ಬಗ್ಗೆ ಒಂದು #bytes ಕೊಡಿ ಅಂದ್ರೂ ಹಿಂದೆ-ಮುಂದೆ ನೋಡ್ತಾರೆ ಇನ್ನೊಂದ್ ವಿಷಯವೆನೆಂದರೆ ನಮ್ಮ ಚಿತ್ರದಲ್ಲಿ ಪ್ರಮುಖ ಪಾತ್ರಕ್ಕೆ ಕನ್ನಡದ ಖ್ಯಾತ 2

column1: can you imagine the wrath that was kept within me? i was shocked beyond belief to know that there are still people out here that cant comprehend what we are fighting for and is ignorant to the point that they don’t even want to be corrected .

we are fighting for those strong women (like my mother) who work equally as hard as men and not getting paid the same .
we are fighting for those girls out there who are trapped within the hands of predators
we are fighting for fundamental rights that we should be receiving .
if fighting for what’s right makes me a pathetic and stupid woman
now let me ask you this

column1: we know the beginning of the week can be a slog
column2: but we’re revving up here at ruman project for our january theme
column3: which we’re very excited to share with you!

column2: we’re going to be focusing on feminism in christianity and islam. we’ll be exploring this through ideas of scholars and activists
column4: and by looking at what intersectionality might mean when exploring identities through a faith lens. we know this is an absolutely huge topic
column5: spanning many different elements across time. as such
column6: we’ll be selective with what we focus on whilst doing our very best to be as inclusive and diverse as possible in our approach - a big challenge you might say! we do not claim to have any ‘answers’ but instead want to create a space for discussion and dialogue.

column1: if there is a particular topic you’d like us to cover or feel that we have missed something important
column2: we would love to hear from you.  we really welcome feedback too
column3: so please feel free to contact us and let us know how we can improve.

column1: 🔸 по поверьям южноамериканских индейцев морфо — это души умерших людей
column3: а местное название этих бабочек можно перевести как «частица неба
которые сорвал ветер. они также называли бабочек «feralis» — «свирепая»

column1: 🔸древние греки считали бабочку символом бессмертия души. психея (греч. «душа») изображалась в образе девушки с крыльями бабочки.

column5: жених перед свадьбой дарит невесте живую или нефритовую бабочку как символ любви.

column1: 🔸с глубочайшим почтением относятся к бабочкам буддисты: ведь именно к бабочке обратился будда со своей проповедью.
🔸в японии нимфалида sasakia charonda является символом страны. по верованиям японцев
column2: бабочка символизирует молодую женщину. порхающие друг вокруг друга бабочки символизируют семейное счастье
column3: а белая бабочка — душу умершего. 🔸у христиан стадии жизненного цикла бабочки олицетворяли жизнь
column5: поэтому бабочку иногда изображали в руке младенца христа как символ возрождения и воскресения души.

column1: مردا اگه با دیدنم تحریک میشن خودشونو کنترل کنن. اونا #نگاه نکنن🚫 چرا من خودمو بپوشونم؟؟😒 ➕گفتم: 👈 اگه شدنی بود و میشد نگاه نکنی یا تحریک نشی که اونهمه کمپین #metoo و #women_not_object لازم نبود!!

غریزه که دستوربردار نیست!! 👈بعدشم فرض کن یه نفر تصمیم گرفته وزن کم کنه، اگه این فرد رو سر سفره‌ای پر از انواع غذاهای خوش‌رنگ و خوش‌مزه😋 قرار بدیم، می‌تونه خودشو کنترل کنه و چیزی نخوره؟؟ حتی اگه اراده‌ش قوی باشه یه ناخنکی به غذاها می‌زنه... ⭕️حالا جوونایی رو در نظر بگیر که امکان #ازدواج ندارن و تو #جامعه با انواع تیپ‌های #تحریک‌_کننده مواجه میشن⚡️😟 به نظرت تو چنین شرایطی چقدر می‌تونن خودشونو کنترل کنن و نگاه نکنن ⁉️😥 وقتی شما حریم‌ها رو رعایت نمی‌کنی چطور انتظار داری مردا بتونن هوس‌شون رو کنترل کنن ⁉️😒 💯 مطمئنا #رعایت_حریم راحت‌تر و اجرایی‌تره تا #کنترل_هوس☝️ 📖 برگرفته از کتاب «تربیت جنسی از منظر قرآن و حدیث»، صفحه ۱۵۱ و ۱۵۲

179711;instagram;2019-01-14 13:20:28;FALSE;it’s here....😭😭😭⁣
today i woke up with one year of sobriety behind me!!⁣

column3: 000 seconds of sobriety with a lifetime to go! ⁣

column1: until i made the decision a year ago to quit
column2: i never thought i could do it. ⁣

column1: i didn’t know that i could do holidays
column4: brunches and stressful days without alcohol. now i know i can! ⁣

column2: “now that you know you can actually go without it
column3: do you think you’ll ever just have a glass here or there?” ⁣

column1: the answer for me is an astounding
i quit drinking because one drink was never enough. ⁣
i quit drinking because it became a tool for me to numb out my emotions. ⁣
i quit drinking because i thought it was easier to escape in a wine bottle than to face my problems. ⁣
i quit drinking because i was using it as a crutch in motherhood. ⁣
i quit drinking because it made me feel like crap and only magnified the issues that i once thought i was using it to help...calming my anxiety and restless sleep. ⁣

column2: alcohol isn’t an option in my life.⁣

column1: so much growth has happened for me in this  last year...and there is still so much healing to come. i’m high on life! 🧘🏼‍♀️⁣

column2: y’all...i’m so damn proud of myself but i didn’t do it alone...⁣

column1: special thanks to god for giving me the power to take control of my own life. ⁣
to danny for supporting me and encouraging me every step of the way with unconditional love. ⁣
to my sister kimberly who started this wild journey with me with very little hesitation. ⁣
and to all of my supporters out there who have done nothing but cheer me on. ⁣
i love all of you and couldn’t be more grateful. ⁣
ps: for those of you out there struggling to get through the tough days without alcohol...i see you. you are loved and you can do hard things!! i’m cheering you on. ⁣

column1: until i made the decision a year ago to quit
column2: i never thought i could do it. ⁣

column1: i didn’t know that i could do holidays
column4: brunches and stressful days without alcohol. now i know i can! ⁣

column2: “now that you know you can actually go without it
column3: do you think you’ll ever just have a glass here or there?” ⁣

column1: the answer for me is an astounding
i quit drinking because one drink was never enough. ⁣
i quit drinking because it became a tool for me to numb out my emotions. ⁣
i quit drinking because i thought it was easier to escape in a wine bottle than to face my problems. ⁣
i quit drinking because i was using it as a crutch in motherhood. ⁣
i quit drinking because it made me feel like crap and only magnified the issues that i once thought i was using it to help...calming my anxiety and restless sleep. ⁣

column2: alcohol isn’t an option in my life.⁣

column1: so much growth has happened for me in this  last year...and there is still so much healing to come. i’m high on life! 🧘🏼‍♀️⁣

column2: y’all...i’m so damn proud of myself but i didn’t do it alone...⁣

column1: 179721;instagram;2019-01-14 13:49:03;FALSE;putting the pieces together #foodbabysoul #foodforthought #piecing #truestory i think about haters making this work. we perceive there are more haters because they can hide behind their phones. the more i watch listen and read about african american history
column2: one naturally pieces together similarities with their present human condition. for example #depression #mentalhealthissues we read reports about how #socialmedia effects your behavior and psyche when you feel ineffective making impossible comparaisons. or take the #metoo movement spotlighting all the sexual harassment and abuse silenced for ages. even the black panther women were asking their men to fight for the dignity and well being of girls. imagine a whole lifetime of being told you are inferior
column3: abused and it being okay to do so by law? why would 1 in 5 immigrants want to come to 🇺🇸? why are 1 in 3 black male babies predicted to be incarcerated in 🇺🇸? 1 in 4 black women have a loved one in 🇺🇸jails? the thoughts and prayers are not working. it might keep people alive in faith but...we need laws passed and the constitution held for its word and not just for toting a gun. the ptsd will be on high valentine's day in parkland
column4: fl. as is loss of any kind. life becomes very simplified and less pitiful when you start realizing how little suffering one does in their own bubble. history unveils the crookedness and mistreatment of people by federal government. one can piece together that reality by finding out if it's all just fiction your being fed. i can understand how 🇺🇸 fell into this current administration but i will never understand any re-election of its kind. i believe it's about time we all pay microscopic attention to the disenfranchised. if you don't like people then consider the 55 elephants killed each day

column1: 179729;instagram;2019-01-14 13:56:01;FALSE;"今日はspa！の「ヤレる女子大学ランキング」に抗議の署名活動をされていた方達のオープンミーティングに参加してきました。
この後spa編集部と対談して、「女性をモノのように扱っていたことを反省する」とコメントしたみたい。
少し前だったら「こんなことで？」と言われるような案件だったと思う。
だけれど、「ヤレる」という言葉に言い表せない不快感、尊厳を傷つけられている感覚を持ってきた女性は少なくないと思う。
ヤレるではなく対等にお互いがしたいと思ったらするのがセックス。
「こういう記事がどうせ男は嬉しいんだろう」というのもそもそも男性に対してとても失礼。こんなランキングを求める日本人男性やべーって世界各国で報道されてしまっている。
少しずつでも、今まで本当に自分は他人をモノ扱いしてこなかったのか？考える場面が増えていけばいいと思う。
昨今の炎上問題を「大袈裟だ」とか「めんどくさい」と思って何も考えていない人は、自分がどれだけ無知で思考停止しているか、恥じた方が良いと思うしそういう人がこうやって炎上するようなことを起こしてしまうことを分かった方が良いと思う。
私も常に気をつけなければ…
それにしても朝方まで飲んでからの参加だったのでめっちゃ二日酔い寝不足でした。

column1: we welcome you to this year’s pathways to vday auditions! pathways to vday is a multicultural and multilingual performance of eve ensler's ""the vagina monologues"". we are looking for brave female-identified/gender neutral individuals to join our pathways performance.
we are pleased to share that the vday.org leadership has given pathways for change
column2: inc. special permission to perform this year in april for sexual assault awareness month! the 2018 performance was plagued by snow and ice
column3: performing later in the year will hopefully get us through our messy snow season to ensure performers and audience safety. we are tremendously grateful to the vday.org team for their spirit and thoughtfulness. “the vagina monologues is made up of various personal monologues read by a diverse group of women. originally
column4: eve ensler performed every monologue herself
column5: with subsequent performances featuring three actresses
column6: and more recent versions featuring a different actress for every role. each of the monologues deals with an aspect of the feminine experience
column7: touching on matters such as sex
column17: the various common names for the vagina or simply as a physical aspect of the body. a recurring theme throughout the piece is the vagina as a tool of female empowerment
column18: and the ultimate embodiment of individuality."" (thank you wikipedia)

column1: 179826;instagram;2019-01-14 15:59:06;FALSE;"so this weeks piece is best viewed as tiles or grid format. it's a work in progress shot and i have great things planned for this piece which is on a brick wall. the scale is aprox 2m x 3m and the most important thing is that this is totally freehand with no grids and aiming to get a human likeness of somebody famous. so when the #metoo social media revolution hit the internet i was surprised (not really) to read that wonder woman herself  was inspired by the whole campaign. lynda carter opened up & says she was sexually abused while playing wonder woman in the iconic '70s tv show.

column1: 179834;instagram;2019-01-14 16:00:49;FALSE;"so this weeks piece is best viewed as tiles or grid format. it's a work in progress shot and i have great things planned for this piece which is on a brick wall. the scale is aprox 2m x 3m and the most important thing is that this is totally freehand with no grids and aiming to get a human likeness of somebody famous. so when the #metoo social media revolution hit the internet i was surprised (not really) to read that wonder woman herself  was inspired by the whole campaign. lynda carter opened up & says she was sexually abused while playing wonder woman in the iconic '70s tv show.
carter discussed the personal experiences that have led her to become such an outspoken supporter of the #metoo movement
column2: which spotlights women chronicling stories of sexual misconduct on social media. a longtime feminist and activist
column3: carter was the symbol in the 1970's show for female power of her time and i remember watching the show along with the bionic woman too. i believed anything was possible for me to achieve when i was a little girl. showing the importance of these tv shows.  sadly even wonderwoman endured the industry's rampant sexual abuse and harassment.

column2: which has played lip service to women's empowerment for decades — all while systematically exploiting and ensuring their oppression.

column1: 179838;instagram;2019-01-14 16:02:22;FALSE;"since last friday this has been burning a hole in my heart
i want to start a conversation about victim blaming - why we do it
column2: where it comes from. an open and honest conversation

column1: after watching a @redtabletalk on ""surviving r. kelly"" i read through some of the comments on here & on fb and was astounded how much victim bashing and blaming was going on. women tearing into other women. to tell you the truth it left me speechless and incredibly sad.

we live in a culture of naming and shaming - and there is a big difference between reporting a crime and naming and shaming! this causes endless damage not just to those we put down but also to ourselves. shaming anyone into anything is harmful and destroys them.
an article in domesticshelters.org states that ""victim shaming happens across the globe every day - survivors of rape
column2: sexual assault & domestic violence face ridicule and judgement for stepping forward & speaking out. sometimes this shaming comes from more than just anonymous comments on the internet
column3: but also their own family & friends as well"".

column1: we blame the victim for everything
column3: but also how and when they choose to tell.

column1: victim blaming is so harmful to all.
it starts with sentences like this
column2: that i come across so very often: ""what was she wearing?"" ""was she drunk?"" ""why does she only come out with it now?"" ""it's the schoolgirls fault for wearing a short skirt that old men ogle her and make advances."" we blame the victim and her behaviour

column1: maybe someone can help me understand why we bash victims.
is it so that we don't have to look at our own lives
is is because of the lies we told our daughters that now come back to haunt us?
is it too painful to watch what is happening
column2: so we push it away by blaming those who were harmed?

column1: why can we not talk about it in an open and honest way? what is stopping us?
it's not a new thing either
column2: but i had hoped that we are ready now to share and be listened to. i was hoping for input and getting a conversation started.

column1: 179843;instagram;2019-01-14 16:04:50;FALSE;"#barbietoo  before i left the house i made sure to dress in something loose that would not be too distracting. as i walk the streets of new york at night
column2: one hand holds my groceries tightly
column3: the other holds my pocket knife. i walk with urgency
column4: my hoodie is up and my headphones in and
column6: act like a barrier between the men who catcalls and whistles at me. i see a masculine shadow at the end of the street
column7: but i cannot see its owner. i fear it’s a man awaiting my passing. i make a detour and walk across the street.

column1: as i usually do on a weekend night
column2: i was clubbing and hanging out with my girls. i normally go to gay clubs
column3: but this weekend i went to a straight club.  once i felt a strong grip on my ass
column4: i turned around to say what the hell
column5: but this 6 foot tall frat guy in a polo would not look at me. this is the first time i  had my ass grabbed unsolicitedly. they have the balls to grab me
column6: but they don’t own up to their actions. every 5 minutes i would take a headcount of my girls because the cocky boys would not listen to us when we said we did not want to grind with them. this was the first night where i saw that the boys were not listening to no. it made me wonder why they felt because it was dark and the music was loud that they could do what they want. i was not being listened to. “there is no greater threat to women than men? we’re the number one threat!” said louis c.k. in his hbo special. when are men taught to acknowledge boundaries? i should be able to leave and feel safe wherever i go without having to worry. i am tired with the way that men are treating me and other women. every women has there own story with harassment

column1: 179889;instagram;2019-01-14 17:02:24;FALSE;"oggi a #donnesulpodio parliamo dell’ennesimo caso di violenza sessuale nello sport femminile.
a denunciare il suo coach è stata shim suk-hee
column2: campionessa sudcoreana di short track (specialità del pattinaggio sul ghiaccio). shim ha presentato lo scorso dicembre una denuncia contro il suo allenatore cho jae-beom
column3: accusandolo di violenze fisiche e psicologiche che avrebbero avuto inizio nel 2014: “mi ha spezzato le dita a colpi di bastone da hockey — ha detto in aula di tribunale la campionessa —
column4: mi colpiva alla testa e al corpo. temevo di morire”. a parlare è una giovane donna esausta
column6: che ha scelto di far sentire la sua voce per denunciare il mostro che doveva darle forza ed invece gliel’ha tolta. una donna coraggiosa
column7: anche perché dobbiamo ricordare che la corea del sud è un paese fortemente conservatore e le vittime di abusi spesso hanno subito “public shaming”. l’ex coach ha ammesso davanti agli organi di polizia di aver picchiato anche altre tre atlete nel periodo di preparazione preolimpica “per migliorare le loro prestazioni”
column8: ma nega l’accusa di violenza sessuale. cho jae-beom è stato condannato a dieci mesi di detenzione.

column1: il messaggio che viene trasmesso da tale vicenda è un messaggio di grande coraggio e di forza.
auguriamo a shim di ricominciare e di continuare a vincere facendo ciò che ama di più: pattinare. ~carlotta

column1: go ahead girl. set that freak straight! learning is rough sometimes. when i learn the most about myself is when i’m in the most pain. its this terrible and wonderful double edged sword of living. i’m so glad to have lived long enough to be able to reflect upon my path. things get touch and go for me sometimes and at key moments i have thought of checking myself out. but i know now nothing will ever hurt me again
column2: not so bad that i won’t be okay. damn passing of time and life experience makes a person smarter sometimes. i wish this author continued strength and the true love of friends in her life. sorry i rambled. this one hit home for me friend. -vu❤️💜⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column1: 179909;instagram;2019-01-14 17:13:40;FALSE;"did you know that pap smears save lives?
regular pap testing catches cervical cancer in early stages and results in women being able to treat the cancer before it progresses further. .
pap smears also catch other uterine problems. a pap smear is when a doctor scrapes the lining of the cervix with a cotton swab to collect some cells. since the cervix is connected to the uterus
column2: a pap test gives a good idea of the patient's uterine health. .
but rather looks for abnormal cervical changes (cervical dysplasia)—precancerous or cancerous cells that could indicate cancer. if any are found
column4: such as a colposcopy or biopsy
column5: will be done in order to diagnose cancer.

column1: the test is named after george papanicolaou
column2: the greek doctor who invented the procedure in the early 1940s.

column1: a 2012 study showed that women who were diagnosed with cervical cancer following a pap screening had a 92% cure rate. the study was conducted in sweden following the country's implementation of regular pap screening.
when was your last pap smear? do you keep up to date on your screenings?

column2: the chicago singer should be able to enjoy his musical legacy.

column1: tmz recently caught up with french montana who shared a contentious opinion on r. kelly. while many are hoping to see r. kelly behind bars
column2: french believes that kellz should be able to enjoy his legacy as an artist regardless of whether he’s a sexual predator or not. the rapper even name-dropped michael jackson while he was at it. “all the greats went down like that
“let somebody enjoy their legacy. whatever happened
column6: mention that these allegations shouldn’t be shocking to anyone. r. kelly did mention it in his songs. french referenced the “bump n grind” line

column2: reading “my playboy” from december 2008. at the time i posed for playboy
column4: trapped in an abusive relationship with myself and someone else who put me down when i looked “pretty”. i felt fat
column7: and playboy was my way to validate myself
column8: and for a few weeks it worked. i was chosen by the late hugh hefner as one of the 55th anniversary playmates! meeting hef and being a guest in his home was certainly the high i craved
column9: but it didn’t last long. shortly after came disappointment when i wasn’t chosen to be an official playmate. finally came the harsh judgment from friends
column11: and peers (today i see that as their fear and jealously of something they couldn’t understand). it continued to be a thorn in my side for many
column12: many years. i found myself feeling rejected from playboy and my real life. i began to try to hide the fact i was even part of the playboy family
column13: although i was extremely proud of myself. i let others make me feel ashamed of expressing myself sexually
column14: and artistically. i had relationships that failed because “i just can’t see the mother of my child having posed for playboy” “my family doesn’t approve”. bosses who held it over my head
column15: sexually harassing me on a regular basis because “that was the kind of girl i was”. this is just a small piece of what went on for almost a decade causing major ptsd.

column2: so incredibly thankful and honored to have been chosen to be a part of this legacy. i’m proud of my journey
column3: my mental and physical health growth. i hope one day i get the chance to share with playboy
column4: my experience and success story with my mental health issues ♥️ thank you to the late hef @hughhefner for giving me such an incredible opportunity to be a part of @playboy thank you to sweet @hollymadison for being so kind to me during my shoot
column5: you made me feel beautiful when i felt like i was nothing. thank you to so many of you that have been following me since the very beginning
column6: i consider you my friends ♥️ thank you to my dear friend @revolvephotog for this wonderful photo #playboy #metoo #mentalhealth #beproudofwhoyouare";;en;#playboy

column2: reading “my playboy” from december 2008. at the time i posed for playboy
column4: trapped in an abusive relationship with myself and someone else who put me down when i looked “pretty”. i felt fat
column7: and playboy was my way to validate myself
column8: and for a few weeks it worked. i was chosen by the late hugh hefner as one of the 55th anniversary playmates! meeting hef and being a guest in his home was ceainly the high i craved
column9: but it didn’t last long. sholy after came disappointment when i wasn’t chosen to be an official playmate. finally came the harsh judgment from friends
column11: and peers (today i see that as their fear and jealously of something they couldn’t understand). it continued to be a thorn in my side for many
column12: many years. i found myself feeling rejected from playboy and my real life. i began to try to hide the fact i was even pa of the playboy family
column13: although i was extremely proud of myself. i let others make me feel ashamed of expressing myself sexually
column14: and aistically. i had relationships that failed because “i just can’t see the mother of my child having posed for playboy” “my family doesn’t approve”. bosses who held it over my head
